.\" Manpage for Techno Bass CLI
.TH TECHNO-BASS 1 "Nov 2025" "Techno Rhythm Engine" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
techno-bass \- generate a minimal MVP bassline from JSON config
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B PYTHONPATH=src python -m techno_engine.bass_cli
.br
.B --config
\fIPATH\fP

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBtechno-bass\fP generates a simple, musical MVP bassline. It places an
anchor at step 0 per bar (alternating root/fifth) and offbeat pulses, then
writes a single-track MIDI file.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --config \fIPATH\fP
Path to a JSON file with the following keys:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBbpm\fP (number) — tempo (default 128)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBppq\fP (integer) — pulses per quarter (default 1920)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBbars\fP (integer) — number of bars (default 4)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBseed\fP (integer) — seed (default 1234)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBout\fP (string) — output MIDI path (default out/bass_mvp.mid)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBroot_note\fP (integer) — bass root note (default 45)

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Generate a 16-bar MVP bassline
.nf
cat > /tmp/bass_cfg.json <<'JSON' && \\
PYTHONPATH=src python -m techno_engine.bass_cli --config /tmp/bass_cfg.json
{
  "bpm": 129, "ppq": 1920, "bars": 16,
  "out": "out/bass_mvp_129.mid", "root_note": 45
}
JSON
.fi

.SH EXIT STATUS
Exits 0 on success; non-zero on invalid config or I/O errors.

.SH SEE ALSO
